1. Core Idea

A personal AI interior-stylist agent that helps users upgrade small spaces in their home with aesthetic, trendy, and budget-friendly designs — without hiring a designer or doing a full renovation.
The agent uses vision AI + generative design + shopping recommendations to deliver instant, actionable micro-makeovers.
2. Target User's painpoints
  Don't have ideas and too many scrolling for upgrade
  See how things look before buying
  Instant shopping list and tight budget
3.  Key AI Superpowers
PLANNING
① Vision Understanding
Upload a photo → agent identifies the space:
Style, colors, lighting
Existing objects
Unused potential

② LLM for chatting with users get what they want
feed 3-5 styles if they don't have ideas
  
③ Budget-Aware Shopping Plan
User sets a budget:
$30 / $50 / $100 / $200
AI finds items on Amazon, Ikea, Target, Wayfair, Etsy
Calculates total cost

④ Spatial Arrangement To-do list

Agent gives step-by-step:
“Replace candle with taller vase”
“Add LED strip behind the counter”
“Use layered textiles for look X”
“Place plant on right side for balance”

⑤ Before → After Simulation

AI generates:
Virtual mockups with realistic look
Tap to switch between different aesthetics

4. business model
user subscription + merchant affliate revenues

5. User jouney 
User took a picture/ update picture --> chat with ai anystyle she want/ select image from several preset options --> ai give what it will look like after --> shopping list --> one click to buy -->to do list to change
                                                                                                                                                     |          |
                                                                                                                                                     |--------- |--> reset budget
